comments: I did notice patterns in the alien words. Each prefix corresponded to a specific shape (wopy-, buvi-, gafi-, zeti-), and each suffix somewhat corresponded to a color. In most cases, the suffix "-coe" applied, but when an object was the color purple, it sometimes ended in "-coh" instead (such as in zeticoh and gaficoh). My main strategy was just to repeat the word in my brain each time that a shape appeared until I felt that I had memorized each rule. I did not use paper or otherwise take notes of the words. Overall, I found the task to be pretty easy and enjoyable once I had recognized and memorized the relevant patterns. Good luck with your research, and be well! :)
